# Kubernetes Blue-Green Deployment 🚀

This project demonstrates how to implement **Blue-Green Deployment in Kubernetes** to achieve **zero-downtime application releases**.

---

# 📘 What is Blue-Green Deployment?

Blue-Green deployment is a strategy used to release new application versions with **zero downtime and minimal risk**.

Two identical environments are maintained:

| Environment | Description |
|---|---|
| Blue | Current live production version |
| Green | New version for testing |

Only **one environment serves production traffic at a time**.

Once the new version is tested successfully, traffic is switched from **Blue → Green**.

---

# 🏗 Architecture

```
           Users
             |
             v
      Kubernetes Service
             |
     --------------------
     |                  |
 Blue Pods (v1)     Green Pods (v2)
 Production          New Version
```

Initially traffic goes to **Blue Pods**.

After validation, traffic switches to **Green Pods**.

